Two men were left critically injured on Wednesday night after they fell three stories at a block of flats on Church Street in Pietermaritzburg. ER24 said its paramedics arrived on the scene just after 8pm‚ to find two men lying in the parking area of the residence. Both had sustained numerous injuries‚ leaving them in a critical condition. The men were treated for their injuries and provided with advanced life support interventions before they were transported to Edendale Provincial Hospital for urgent treatment.